div1.p: In the District Court, Of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, for the County of King. HABEAS CORPUS.

The People of the United States of America, to the Sheriff of King County To J.C. Mitchell Chief of Police Seattle Greeting: We command you, that you have the body of Geo W. Anderson by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said Geo W. Anderson shall be called or charged, before the HON. RICHARD A. JONES, Judge of the aforesaid Court at Seattle forthwith to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning him the said Geo. W. Anderson And have you then and there this writ. WITNESS THE HON. Richard A. Jones CH Hanford Judge of the said District Court, and the seal thereof this 1st day of October A.D. 1889. RM Hopkins Clerk.

Territory of Washington King County ss. J.C. Mitchell Chief of Police of it City of Seattle in King County as henly empty. That J.C. has the petitioner Geo. W. Anderson under arrest and in my custody.
